 Details Hidden


Catamount Ventures LLC

                                    Catamount Ventures focuses on seed and early-stage investments in the technology and green/clean/sustainable environmental sectors. The firm's 'green' investment mandate seeks investment opportunities with world class entrepreneurs with innovative ideas across all sectors of the economy including but not limited to food, air, water, transportation, materials, alternative energy and energy reduction. Catamount Ventures' technology investments focus on consumer Internet and enterprise technology companies.                                




 Details Hidden


Pelion Venture Partners

                                    Pelion Venture Partners focuses on investments in early-stage companies. The firm target companies operating in the fields of digital media, infrastructure & storage, medical & healthcare, security and software/ SaaS companies. They are hands-on in their approach and work collaboratively on each portfolio company over the life of an investment. The firm partners benefit from their insights and their abilities to focus strategically and tactically on success. They can tap into and leverage a vast network of technology executives in all corners of the IT industry to help their companies achieve success.                                




 Details Hidden


Michael & Susan Dell Foundation

                                    The Michael & Susan Dell Foundation aims to improve outcomes for underserved children. It funds programs that foster and improve the education, health and safety of children. The Foundation's programs include urban education, childhood health, and family economic stability.The Michael & Susan Dell Foundation was founded in 1999. Its headquarters are located in Austin, TX.                                




 Details Hidden


Trinity Ventures LP

                                    Trinity Ventures focuses on investments in technology and consumer start-up companies including clean technology, consumer, infrastructure, services and software. Their specific areas of interest include: advertising, cloud computing, digital media, e-commerce, enterprise 2.0, financial services, gaming, lead generation, marketplace, mobile, networking, open source, SaaS, security, systems management, UGC, vertical content, video and wireless.                                






